PSA: #Rstats "recycles" indices when two vectors have different sizes. e.g.:

x <- 1:10
subset <- c(T, F)
x[subset]
[1] 1 3 5 7 9 

Output is not '1' as you might expect. This can lead to hard-to-debug errors if this isn't what you intend, as there's no error message or warning.
